caption: I get to eat here a lot since I work right next to it. I like how their customer service is always great and they keep the spot clean at all times. Prices are reasonable and they serve generous portions.

I celebrated my nomination today in this great place. I am glad to say that it was a cool evening and the place was definitely the reason for this outstanding meeting. The stuff  participated in a sweet manner, the cooking was yummy and my friends were very  overjoyed. We shall absolutely visit again for more events. thanks very much.
Korean food at this spot - great. entered near nine, it wasn't busy. definitely worth going back to.
The service is regularly speedy, fantastic character, very friendly staff. Will eat here again when I am in town.

The girl that works the bar with the dreads was awesome her personality down to her drinks everything was just amazing with her, however I didn’t like the fact that the bell in our room didn’t work so we had to keep coming out to the bar in order to get drinks but she made it better with her customer service skills such a people person we will definitely be back thanks to her.

The music also kept changing pitch and speed with no explanation or solution. The workers were friendly and the drinks were good. Food was not the best you’d get a better value somewhere else in the area. Probably won’t come back.

Love this karaoke bar, lots of great drinks and great location on 18th Street. Big rooms make for a fun time and lots of friends are able to come together. The only problem is that there's so many songs to choose from, you almost need another hour to account for the decision-making time.
Fun place for a birthday party or any Saturday night
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I love how their customer service is always awesome and they keep the place clean at all times. Rates are affordable and they serve big portions.

This place isn't for sober people who can only read English. Meant mostly for Chinese (?) people since English is only a secondary (or maybe even tertiary) language. Good parts are that you can reserve by phone and if you don't stay your full time, you can end early and pay by the minute. Great service for ordering drinks. No public karaoke so not as fun as it could be (unless there was in the crowded bar area and I couldn't notice or enjoy it).

Staff was amazing, honestly who doesn't love karaoke.
Nice atmosphere but our mics didn't work which took up 15 minutes of our time for the room and we ended up being rushed by staff. Songbook also needs to be updated.

Karaoke rooms are private, allowing you to sing your heart out without being viewed by hundreds of strangers, but the korean food was far from the best Ive ate. The appetizers were great but everything else left us wishing we went to one of the other korean food places on the strip

So much fun!! All of the staff were so friendly and helpful. My tip would be to go early and stay late. The only thing I would like different is to have newer songs separated out. Which they may have been, but I didn't find them like that. And add Lizzo!

The food was excellent. The service was great. The rooms could have been updated or had pillows for the hard seats we sat on  Also the fees, well that's another story. The price could be reasonable. But all in all I enjoyed my 34th birthday.
A secret place in Adams Morgan that will give you a lifetime experience.

I visited here with a few coworkers to celebrate a birthday and it was a really fun experience! They open at 5 and usually stay open late on both weekdays and weeknights. It was really simple to make a reservation, and we did so within 2 days of our event. The room sizes are great, the song selection is awesome, and it is a cool way to do karaoke without being on a stage in front of strangers. I'll definitely be returning!
Fun place
Innacurate - overpriced.

This place offers karaoke in private rooms, you rent them out for an hour or so. The staff is helpful!! The rooms are clean... The music choices aren't overly new but there are a lot of choices. Great place for karaoke with a group of friends.

First of all, this place is waaaaaaay too expensive for what it’s worth. The food, service and music selection and everything that’s there isn’t worth the prices. I MOST DEFINITELY WON’T BE COMING BACK. PERIOD.

I WILL SAY I WENT TONIGHT 5/24/2019  AND OVERALL THE PLACE IS VERY COZY,  IT LOOKS BETTER IN PERSON THAN IT DOES ONLINE. THE KOREANS/ASIANS/PHILIPPINES STAFF THAT WORKED THERE [90% OF THE STAFF] WEREN'T FRIENDLY AT ALL. THE REMAINING 10% OF STAFF WERE AFRICAN- AMERICANS AND THEY WERE VERY FRIENDLY AND HOSPITABLE. THE ROOMS WERE A GOOD SIZE DEPENDING ON YOUR RESERVATION AND PARTY SIZE. THE SETUP KAOROKE SYSTEM IN DIFFERENT ROOMS [ AT LEAST TWO -THREE TVS,  AND MULTIPLE SPEAKERS] 3 MICS, TAMBOURINES WAS PRETTY DOPE. UNFORTUNATELY,  THE TV AND MICS TEND TO "GO OUT" IN THE MIDDLE OF A SONG EVERY NOW AND THEN. IF IT CONTINUES TO HAPPEN,  COMMUNICATE IT TO THE HOST/HOSTESS- THEY WOULD CHECK IT OUT AND THEN BE HAPPY TO MOVE YOU EVENTUALLY. OVERALL, THE ENVIRONMENT WAS DIVERSED, CLASSY OR LITTY IF NEED BE. I ENJOYED THE UP TO DATE SONGS [ FOR THE MOST PART] AND HOW IT KIND OF FELT LIKE IT WAS YOUR OWN PRIVATE PARTY. I WOULD RECOMMEND FOR SOME FRIDAY NIGHT FUN...BUT DON'T EXPECT TOO MUCH FROM MANAGEMENT.

Fun place to karaoke with your own small or large group. Been twice now, there is a very large song selection and sophisticated system, they teach you how to use it and it's not very hard to start queuing up songs. Definitely need to book a room ahead of time, when I was leaving there were people coming in looking to sing but every room was booked.
Definitely would recommend. Amazingly delicious food at affordable prices.
Smells like farts when you walk in but the hotbox karaoke rooms are fun

Went during HAPPY HOUR, just my husband and I, and the bill was $72 (which was discounted $15)!!! This included the $20 room, $20 pitcher which was really a carafe, and $14 snack. Doesn’t add up right? It is because they added gratuity and a karaoke tax. I would have been cool with the price if the karaoke room wasn’t soooooo bad. The mics didn’t work properly, the room was extremely small, and it took more time to learn how to work the machine than we actually had to sing songs. I was extremely disappointed as this was an anniversary activity. If I could give no stars, I would. It is NOT worth the time, money, or energy going to this awful place. SERIOUSLY!!! This place has 3 stars for a reason. Frankly, I am surprised the rating isn’t lower than that.

Mics were on wrong frequency. Worker did not know how to calibrate. Ended up moving us rooms. New room did not have sound. Once we had everything fixed, we had already burned over half of our time. still charged us full price and then $12 extra for gratuity? I'm never stingy about service fees but in this case there wasn't even an acceptable level of service. Go here if you want to ruin a night
Karaoke is amazing
Had an amazing time!  Food was great! Drinks were great! Music was awesome!
If i could give them zero star, I’d... food was so bad.. and it’s so expensive for it’s food and service. If you guys have money to go here, i wanna recommend u to give that money to homeless people

Hey , had my birthday there .... reservation was at 7pm got there around 7:15, the reservation was not altered although there was a grace period. Was rushed out after reservation and over charged ! My party and the waitress was instructed not to purchase on the room , entire party went to bar to order and pay separately from room. Still charged room card for other orders, as well as had card and receipt of group member at bar , confused at the over charging, lack of customer service and communication , was not offered anything as well as she swiped my card twice!  when told about the over charge, the card at the bar and orders on room she became flustered and aggressive, shoed off other guest trying to check out, swiped my card for the over charged refunded me and then had to charge my card for original price ! Smh I wouldn’t recommend this spot go to wok and roll across the street ! Cheaper and maybe better service , they just want your money here and will not accommodate or offer anything! Poor customer service , rude service, lack of communication, over charging and language barrier ! Everything is ok until you get there !
Loved it had a great experience staff was very helpful and service was great!!!

Booked a room for Saturday night for a bachelorette party. Booked hotels just for this event. They messed up our reservation and gave away our time slot. Offered nothing to remedy the situation. Shotty reservation system and no customer service. Wasted hundred on this failed event. No trust left.
Fun AND good TIMES!

My friends and I were there last night for my sister’s birthday and we got terrible customer service. We originally had reservations from 8:30-11pm and had an email confirmation. My sister asked to change to a bigger room and asked if we could still get the reservation until 11pm and the manager agreed. Around 10pm the karaoke stopped working and we were told we had to leave, we were confused because the manager originally said we could stay until 11pm. The manager proceeded to call my sister a liar and said she super late to the reservation anyway. My sister got there at 8:32 and wasn’t checked in until 8:35; the whole experience here was just terrible. The manager could not find a way to accommodate use in the situation she created. We were having so much fun doing karaoke and lost an hour trying to find a solution. When we left no one else was even using the room we were in. This definitely ruined my sister’s birthday. Horrible customer service by the manager who couldn’t even communicate clearly.
They weren't even open Sunday night, when their website says they were supposed to be

Came here while on a work trip, I'm not a karaoke person but the group had fun and the food was good. They also have this cinnamon tea in a can..... It might be the best thing I've ever drank 8n my 30 years on earth.

Here with some colleagues for the karaoke. What's nice is they have private rooms you can rent by the hour. The place we had could hold 6-8 people. Good experience.  Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz
Good drink specials. Didn't try the food. Karoke was amazing.

Muzette over charged us for mutilple drinks to the tune of $800 when it should have been closer to $400. Then called the police when we pushed back on the charges because it was “after hours” and they wanted to go home. We had a really fun time but it was awful when we tried to pay our bill. Double what we ordered? So ridiculous. We paid for what we order but refused to pay for items added on that we did not ask for. Beware of added charges.

This is probably the best karaoke spot in DC. There are two negatives: 1) the terrible videos for some of the songs (though I don't think there's much they can do about that). 2) the software for music selection is god awful. That problem seems fixable.

Fun place to go with a group and good food!

Karaoke in front of strangers can be intimidating. Alcohol helps. So does renting a room and filling it with supportive friends.  The location is perfect, right in Adams Morgan. I would highly recommend starting your evening here and then moving on to another bar/restaurant for more drinks and some food.
Nice place for karaoke

Came here for a girls night out to celebrate a birthday and couldn't wait to try it! If you love food and karaoke, this is your jam. There were about 10 fo us and we started with dinner, ordering almost the entire menu so we could share and try everything—I was in heaven. Trying everything is my favorite way to eat. We had a reservation for a private karaoke room and OMG was it fun! Our very friendly server kept our drinks full and we ran the karaoke machine ourselves. No one is shy when the door closes and they get to sing to friendly faces! It was like one big group sing a long that I never wanted to stop. We are already planning the next hoorah.
we went for karaoke... it was sad that we were the only group there that night, but good times! would def go again

The food was good. The drinks were good. The crowds was horrible and the place was packed to capacity. And I'm not a fan of karaoke. If I liked it there would be another star. My little brother did so another star. There ya go!

They just randomly came in and said last song. The software was kinda jumbled and confusing to work with sometime the boom would have a song but it wouldn't show up in search but if you type in the song number it works.

It's hard to beat private room karaoke! This subterranean space has about a dozen karaoke rooms that are rented by the hour (be sure to make a reservation in advance). You can order drinks at the bar or from the staff that pop by frequently to see if you need anything. The song selection process can be a bit tricky at first, but there are thousands of songs to select from. It can get pretty hot in the rooms, so dress accordingly!

Sing all you want in the privacy of your own room with wide variety of popular singers of  other old and present. Much fun to be a had whether in a larger group or on a date. Much variety of songs and liquor to help you ease through some of the tougher chords musically. Have fun, and drink and sing responsibly here. Kudos

Great to do Asia-style, private room kareoke. We had some sound problems from time to time, but it's unclear whether it was a hardware or software based problem. The Korean/Japanese song list was limited, but had an impressive list for English! No shortage of things to sing.

Awful interface for music selection and really outdated stuff, but at least it's open late. Good selection of music I suppose if you speak any Asian languages...or sing in them for that matter. Awful visuals.

Prices at this Adams Morgan staple are on the more expensive side at 45 bucks per hour.  We found their music system to be hard to use and not intuitive -- for example searching for an artist required us to select by ID, type in their name, press cancel, then attach the artist into our queue.  Searching was generally poor as well -- searching for an artist might not bring up the artist, but using their ID would -- it was a mess. Service was on point though, and they were very attentive to their patrons (this is what saved this review from a 2 star).  Unfortunately (or fortunately depending on how you look at it) this is the only local karaoke bar in the area so you are kind of stuck with what you got.   I hope they work to upgrade their rooms and pricing structure.
Great place for cool dishes and well made cocktails
I literally don't remember my time here. I think that means it must have been fun...

Main draw to this place is the Karaoke, but the bar and restaurant aren't half bad. Some of the Korean dishes are a bit hit or miss but the classics (e.g. Bibimbap) would compete with some of the best that DC has to offer.
Karaoke and liquor. I've never had their food
Korean karaoke joint. Can't go wrong for a good time.

Absolutely the worst karaoke system I've seen. A few years ago this place was great, but they got rid of their good system and selection in favor of a touch screen system that's impossible to navigate, and that's when the system is working and not freezing or showing error messages on the screen. Selection of songs is good only if you're into the latest American pop songs and Korean songs.

My first experience was great a year ago.  The experience I had today at checkout was rather bothering.  We originally went there on the spur of the moment and we were told that they had a lot of reservations at a certain time.  We got there at 5:15pm and time surpassed when speaking to the cashier.  We didn't get to the room until 5:30pm and had difficulties in the room and had to ask for assistance more the one.  She booked us at two hours depending on the reservations that were coming in.  After an hour we decided it was time to go so we went to check out and they tried to charge us for more than an hour and we were only in there for an hour. I hated the customer service I received upon check out from the black girl with the screwed up hair weave and the bar back that didn't have a clue.  Watch your time when you go there so you won't get ripped off even for s penny.

Friendly staff and great place to sing with friends. I was here last night and had some mandu and kimchi. The meat mandu was very good and the kimchi was average. The prices are on the high side here. If you like karaoke you'll like it here. The rooms are private so you can sing with your friends all night long.
I loved not having to sign a list and waiting forever to sing.

Wife's surprise bday party here, in a private room, was a smash hit! Solidly good selection of songs, combined with good Korean small plates. Staff and party coordinator were all very helpful and accommodating. We had a minor tech issue with a microphone, but this did not detract from the fun experience.  Party goers enjoyed so much that they returned the next day to continue the karaoke-ing!

One of the few karaoke places in DC proper with private rooms. Selection is merely decent, not broadly diverse with western music (bulk is Asian artists, written in the electronic control panel in Asian). Control interface isn't the best as well, it was confusing to a number of folks in my party. Prices are based on party sizes. They offer Korean food which is decent as well. If you want to get your karaoke groove on especially in private rooms format, this is the place.

Your only option for karaoke rooms in DC.  Their Karaoke book is based in Korea, so it has a lot of Korean options as well as Chinese and Japanese.  It is seriously lacking in English options though.  The interface and navigation for the queue system is atrocious.  Book are only by Song title and they don't have books by artist.  But if you want to do Karaoke in a private room in DC, this is your only option.
Only Asian style karaoke place with individual room that's within the district proper could be a little cheaper but still all in all reasonably priced and a good time
only 70,000 songs?  That's weak. The KJs in Annapolis have 400,000 & touchscreens that work.

Pricey, but the only room-style in the DC area. The song selection isn't great.  And the rooms were upgraded with touchscreens, which actually makes it harder to enter songs since it can be pretty packed and it's easier to just pass the remote around. Maybe if they could ruggedize some tablets to use as the interface without losing too much money from inevitable breakages. The food looks good, though I've never eaten any. Staff is very friendly!
Asian style Karaoke. Individual rooms with karaoke setups. Somewhat overpriced but the only Karaoke place within DC to have individual rooms.

Bibim Bap $12 (4/5 NOMs) lets sing a song and eat some, Its the multi layer of nomnom goodness. I just love the super runny sunny side up egg on top of veggies, beef bulgogi and rice. Rice was nice and sticky and prepared perfectly for chopstick. Just make sure to have a little bit of everything in every bite. That thing really filled me up. Only thing, this dish was a bit too spicy for me. I would defiantly order this again while signing some killer karaoke songs like Aqua Barbie Girl!

This place combines two features I find enjoyable - Korean food and karaoke. I cannot say that you can go there with the intention of combining both but it is still good to know that a dinner out can turn to a karaoke night.
Spendy but with a friendly staff. Not a place to go w/ a group you don't know real well, unless you pre-funked quite a bit.

GREAT chicken bulgolgi! Man, it was sooo good. The banchan was delicious, although I think the cabbage kimchi might have been past its prime. They have a great alcohol selection, too. Service was good. The karaoke (moraebang) selection was great, too! But they don't have multiple languages in every room, the small room they gave us wasn't terribly appealing looking and it was cold in there!!!
